<summary>
The <strong><c>mask-border-source</c></strong> <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS">CSS</see> property sets the source image used to create an element&amp;apos;s <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/mask-border">mask border</see>.
</summary>
<remarks>
<para>The <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/mask-border-slice">mask-border-slice</see> property is used to divide the source image into regions, which are then dynamically applied to the final mask border.</para>
